verses.text_plain: O God, my heart is fixed; I will sing and give praise, even with my glory.
verses.verse_html: 1O God, my heart is fixed; I will sing and give praise, even with my glory.

verses.text_plain: Awake, psaltery and harp: I myself will awake early.
verses.verse_html: 2Awake, psaltery and harp: I myself will awake early.

verses.text_plain: I will praise thee, O Lord, among the people: and I will sing praises unto thee among the nations.
verses.verse_html: 3I will praise thee, O Lord, among the people: and I will sing praises unto thee among the nations.

verses.text_plain: For thy mercy is great above the heavens: and thy truth reacheth unto the clouds.
verses.verse_html:
4For thy mercy is great above the heavens: and thy truth reacheth unto the clouds. ▼
▼ clouds: or, skies

verses.text_plain: Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens: and thy glory above all the earth;
verses.verse_html: 5Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens: and thy glory above all the earth;

verses.text_plain: That thy beloved may be delivered: save with thy right hand, and answer me.
verses.verse_html: 6That thy beloved may be delivered: save with thy right hand, and answer me.

verses.text_plain: God hath spoken in his holiness; I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem, and mete out the valley of Succoth.
verses.verse_html: 7God hath spoken in his holiness; I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem, and mete out the valley of Succoth.

verses.text_plain: Gilead is mine; Manasseh is mine; Ephraim also is the strength of mine head; Judah is my lawgiver;
verses.verse_html: 8Gilead is mine; Manasseh is mine; Ephraim also is the strength of mine head; Judah is my lawgiver;

verses.text_plain: Moab is my washpot; over Edom will I cast out my shoe; over Philistia will I triumph.
verses.verse_html: 9Moab is my washpot; over Edom will I cast out my shoe; over Philistia will I triumph.

verses.text_plain: Who will bring me into the strong city? who will lead me into Edom?
verses.verse_html: 10Who will bring me into the strong city? who will lead me into Edom?

verses.text_plain: Wilt not thou, O God, who hast cast us off? and wilt not thou, O God, go forth with our hosts?
verses.verse_html: 11Wilt not thou, O God, who hast cast us off? and wilt not thou, O God, go forth with our hosts?

tokens.text: and wilt not thou, O God

verses.text_plain: Give us help from trouble: for vain is the help of man.
verses.verse_html: 12Give us help from trouble: for vain is the help of man.

verses.text_plain: Through God we shall do valiantly: for he it is that shall tread down our enemies.
verses.verse_html: 13Through God we shall do valiantly: for he it is that shall tread down our enemies.
